<HEADLINE>
FT  12 NOV 93 / International Capital Markets: Mexican group plans global
offer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
GRUPO Financiero Serfin, the Mexican finance house, filed a registration
statement with the Securities and Exchange Commission for a global offering
of 6.5m American depository shares and 9m series L limited voting shares in
Mexico, AP reports from Mexico.
The company said it would offer the ADSs, each representing four series L
shares, through an underwriting syndicate managed by CS First Boston, Morgan
Stanley and Serfin Securities.
The company said it would make the 9m L share offering through a Mexican
syndicate in Mexico, and the Mexican government would sell 5m of the L
shares. The offering price for the ADSs would be determined by the price for
its series B shares on the Mexican stock exchange.
