<HEADLINE>
FT  12 NOV 93 / International Company News: Air Canada turnround continues
in quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A LEANER, more competitive Air Canada continued its turnround in the third
quarter despite slow economic recovery and slack operating revenues.
It reported third-quarter operating revenues of CDollars 1.03bn (USDollars
795m), up 2 per cent from a year earlier, and operating income of CDollars
94m, against CDollars 39m. It was the fourth consecutive year-to-year gain
at the operating level and an improvement over the June quarter.
Final net profit was CDollars 43m, or 56 cents a share (fully diluted),
against a loss of CDollars 14m, or 19 cents.
For the nine months, revenues rose slightly to CDollars 2.73bn and operating
income was CDollars 82m, against a loss of CDollars 97m. After restructuring
and financial charges, the net loss was CDollars 236m, or CDollars 3.20,
against a loss of CDollars 307m or CDollars 4.14.
Air Canada has raised about CDollars 200m with the issue of 35m units at
CDollars 5.75 per unit to an underwriting group led by RBC Dominion
Securities. Each unit comprises one new common share and one half a warrant.
A full warrant will allow the holder to buy one Air Canada share for
CDollars 6.25 over the next two years.
</TEXT>
