FT  12 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Densitron denies expansion in Japan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr David Ling, finance director Densitron International, the electronic
components manufacturer, said yesterday the company had 'no specific' plans
to expand into Japan.
Earlier, speculation that the company was planning to make a significant
acquisition in the country had lifted the company's share price by 6p to
36p.
Mr Ling said he knew of no other reason for the rise in the share price.
</TEXT>
