FT  12 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Amber Day sells import division
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AMBER DAY Holdings, the discount retailer, has agreed to sell its import and
distribution division Dennis Day to its current management.
The Amber Day board had decided earlier in the year to dispose of the
division and return to its What Everyone Wants core retail chain. Earlier
this month the group revealed that pre-tax losses for the year to July 31
were reduced to Pounds 2.09m (Pounds 7.75m). Dennis Day incurred losses,
after provisions and before interest and tax, of Pounds 4.6m on turnover
Pounds 8.7m. At July 31, it had net liabilities of Pounds 4.1m.
Amber Day will receive Pounds 659,000 of book debts. The consideration for
the sale of the shares is Pounds 1.
