<HEADLINE>
FT  12 NOV 93 / Arts: Museum of London music festival
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A world music festival celebrating the capital's abundance of traditional
music is to be held on November 20-21 at the Museum of London. A part of the
museum's new exhibition, The Peopling of London, it includes music from
Irish, Jewish and Somali groups.
On the Saturday Taxi Pata Pata present jazz from Zaire in an evening
concert. On Sunday afternoon, broadcaster Andy Kershaw presents traditional
London music which includes Dishari, an East End ensemble playing Bengali
folk music and Royte Klezmores, an all woman East European trio playing
wedding music. Entry on Sunday is free.
The main exhibition, which runs until May 15 1994, looks at London's current
ethnic and cultural diversity in the historical perspective of 15,000 years
of settlement from overseas.
The Peopling of London, Museum of London, London Wall, London EC2.
</TEXT>
