<HEADLINE>
FT  12 NOV 93 / European obstacle to coach seatbelts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GARDNER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE European Commission yesterday acknowledged that the UK cannot introduce
tighter seatbelt laws for coaches and buses in the wake of Wednesday's coach
accident in Kent in which 10 people died, David Gardner writes.
Under European legislation a coach or bus can get a 'single passport' for
the whole of the European Union. The UK or any other member state can
introduce more stringent rules but only enforce them against operators and
manufacturers which seek approval at national rather than European level.
The commission has been trying to amend the legislation and has the support
of the UK, Germany, Ireland and Denmark, but has so far failed to secure a
qualified majority among the 12 member states.
</TEXT>
