FT  12 NOV 93 / The new curbs on Tripoli
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A freeze on all 'funds and financial resources' owned or controlled directly
or indirectly by the Libyan government or any Libyan undertaking or any
individual acting on behalf of either. This excludes all funds derived by
Libya from the sale of oil, gas or petroleum products. These funds must be
paid into bank accounts specifically for this purpose.
The closure of all Libyan Arab Airlines offices in all UN member countries
and a ban on all transactions with the state carrier.
A ban on supply of all aircraft or aviation components or of aircraft
engineering or maintenance services.
Confirmation all states shall 'significantly cut the level of staff at
Libyan diplomatic missions'.
A ban on export to Libya of specific oil transportation and refining
equipment.
