FT  11 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Foster Wheeler and John Wood venture
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
John Wood Group and Foster Wheeler have acquired from the JP Kenny group its
worldwide engineering companies other than those in the former Soviet Union.
The deal is worth about Pounds 5m, including a capital injection by the
purchasers.
A new company, JP Kenny Engineering, has been formed to take over all the
specialist pipeline and undersea engineering services. It has an estimated
turnover of Pounds 14m for the first nine months of this year, and about 320
full-time employees worldwide.
John Wood, based in Aberdeen, is the UK's largest indigenous oil services
company, and Foster Wheeler is the UK subsidiary of Foster Wheeler
Corporation, the US engineering company. The two companies, which already
have joint ventures together, said that JP Kenny's expertise would expand
their services to the oil and gas industries.
