<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Henderson Admin 40% ahead after TR buy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN, Personal Finance Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A LOSS OF pension fund clients failed to stop Henderson Administration
Group, the fund management group, from enjoying a 40 per cent jump in
interim pre-tax profits from Pounds 6.55m to Pounds 9.17m in the six months
to September 30.
The company said client withdrawals lost it about Pounds 500m of pension
fund money. This was 'partly due to the expected withdrawals following the
Touche Remnant acquisition, partly due to a move to indexation by some
clients but also to the residual effects of our previous period of
underperformance'.
However, funds under management at September 30 were Pounds 12.2bn, compared
with Pounds 7.3bn at the interim stage last year. An important factor in the
increase was the acquisition of Touche Remnant, which brought in Pounds
2.2bn of funds. Strong stock markets and inflows in the non-pension fund
side also helped.
At end-September the company had Pounds 4.4bn of pension funds under
management, Pounds 3.2bn of investment trusts and about Pounds 2bn of unit
trusts. After the end of the half, the group launched its first investment
trust under the combined Henderson TR banner and raised Pounds 100m for a
Japanese smaller companies fund.
Total revenues for the first half were Pounds 30.3m, against Pounds 20.5m,
which did not include a full contribution from TR. Operating expenses were
Pounds 22.2m (Pounds 16.7m) but the company said the best comparison was
with last year's second half figure of Pounds 21.3m, which it cited as
evidence that it was controlling costs.
Net interest receivable slumped to Pounds 944,000 (Pounds 2.46m) because of
lower interest rates and the cost of the TR acquisition. After tax of Pounds
3.1m (Pounds 2.82m), earnings per share were 28.23p (21.38p). The interim
dividend is being maintained at 12.5p.
</TEXT>
